From: SBE1V1K LEDE PPE port
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: export PoC cache helpers for NSS-DP

The QSDK NSS-DP driver directly maintains cache coherency for its EDMA
descriptor and packet fast paths.  QSDK kernels expose private dmac_*()
helpers, while upstream arm64 provides the equivalent PoC primitives but
does not export them to modules.

Export the two existing primitives used by NSS-DP.  The driver uses the
full-barrier variants for both regular and former no-DSB call sites.

--- a/arch/arm64/mm/dma-mapping.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/mm/dma-mapping.c
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@
  */
 
 #include <linux/gfp.h>
+#include <linux/export.h>
 #include <linux/cache.h>
 #include <linux/dma-map-ops.h>
 #include <xen/xen.h>
@@ -13,6 +14,9 @@
 #include <asm/cacheflush.h>
 #include <asm/xen/xen-ops.h>
 
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(dcache_clean_poc);
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(dcache_inval_poc);
+
 void arch_sync_dma_for_device(phys_addr_t paddr, size_t size,
 			      enum dma_data_direction dir)
 {
